@startuml desired_001_component_layers
title UC Life Sim - desired component layers (post-Wave-3 pin)

' This diagram pins the layer shape after Waves 1-3 of the architecture-cleanup
' arc. It is not a Wave-5+ projection: per-world singletons, per-trait save
' registration, render snapshot type pinning, and the multi-world explicit-World
' contract are tracked in arch/desired/README.md as future work.
'
' Rule: data flows DOWN. Engine consumes game-asset content via typed loaders
' only; engine packages MUST NOT hard-code UC-Life-specific data shapes.
' ASCII-only labels (em-dashes garble under Java's default Windows charset).

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Inter, sans-serif"
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam ranksep 18
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam rectangle {
  BorderColor #888
  FontSize 12
}
skinparam package {
  BorderColor #555
  FontSize 13
  FontStyle bold
}
top to bottom direction

' --- game-asset band: UC-Life-specific content only ---
package "game asset (UC-Life-specific)" as P_GAME #fafaee {
  rectangle "config\n.json5 -> loaders, read once at boot"          as L_CFG  #f3f6fa
  rectangle "data\nstatic content (scenes, jobs, ships, ...)"       as L_DATA #f3f6fa
}

' --- engine band: reusable across other games ---
package "engine (reusable)" as P_ENG #f0f6ff {
  ' rank 0: composition root
  rectangle "boot\nmain.tsx, autosave, save/debug handler manifests" as L_BOOT #ffffff

  rectangle "procgen\npure, seeded -- roads -> blocks -> cells"     as L_PROC #eef5ee
  rectangle "ecs\nkoota traits + Map<SceneId, World>"               as L_ECS  #fff8ec
  together {
    rectangle "ai\nmistreevous BT (trees + agent)"                  as L_AI   #fff3e6
    rectangle "sim\nclock, scene, loop, ship, events bus"           as L_SIM  #fff3e6
  }
  rectangle "systems\n28 files (vitals, work, npc, combat, ...)"    as L_SYS  #fff3e6
  together {
    rectangle "save\nidb-keyval + handler registry"                 as L_SAVE #f0e6ff
    rectangle "render\npixi + sprite + portrait"                    as L_REND #e9f3ff
  }
  rectangle "ui\nReact DOM + zustand stores"                        as L_UI   #e9f3ff
}

' --- hidden ranking spine: forces strict vertical stack ---
L_CFG  -[hidden]-> L_DATA
L_DATA -[hidden]-> L_BOOT
L_DATA -[hidden]-> L_PROC
L_BOOT -[hidden]-> L_PROC
L_PROC -[hidden]-> L_ECS
L_ECS  -[hidden]-> L_AI
L_ECS  -[hidden]-> L_SIM
L_AI   -[hidden]-> L_SYS
L_SIM  -[hidden]-> L_SYS
L_SYS  -[hidden]-> L_SAVE
L_SYS  -[hidden]-> L_REND
L_SAVE -[hidden]-> L_UI
L_REND -[hidden]-> L_UI

' --- intended (downward) dependency direction ---
L_CFG  --> L_DATA
L_DATA --> L_PROC
L_DATA --> L_ECS
L_PROC --> L_ECS
L_ECS  --> L_SIM
L_AI   --> L_SYS
L_SIM  --> L_SYS
L_SYS  --> L_REND
L_SYS  --> L_SAVE
L_REND --> L_UI
L_BOOT --> L_REND
L_BOOT --> L_UI

' Boot's reach into save and sim is the canonical composition-root pattern
' (handler manifests + autosave binding + DEV-gated debug handles). It is not
' a violation; the seam was inverted in Waves 1, 1.5, 3.
L_BOOT --> L_SAVE
L_BOOT --> L_SIM

note right of L_BOOT
  boot reaches sim/systems/save through three
  registries; concentration is gone.
   - src/boot/autosaveBinding.ts subscribes to
     sim/events.ts ('day:rollover','hyperspeed:start',
     'load:start','load:end'); save and loop no
     longer import each other.
   - src/boot/saveHandlers/* (16 cluster files)
     side-effect-register against src/save/registry.ts;
     save/index.ts iterates handlers blindly.
   - src/boot/debugHandles/* (8 cluster files)
     register against src/debug/uclifeHandle.ts;
     main.tsx dynamic-imports the manifest behind
     import.meta.env.DEV. Rollup tree-shakes it from
     prod. Pattern is canonical, not a violation.
end note

note right of L_SYS
  Systems still hold module-level singletons
  (combat, population, relations, npc buckets,
  activeZone, vitals, stress, supplyDrain,
  spaceSim, engagement). Future: hoist to a
  per-world WorldState trait so multi-world
  isolation stops depending on world count
  being small and fixed. Tracked as Wave 5
  candidate in arch/desired/README.md.
end note

note bottom of P_GAME
  Engine consumes game-asset content via
  typed loaders only (config/index.ts,
  data/*.json5 + ?raw + json5.parse).
  Engine packages MUST NOT hard-code
  UC-Life-specific data shapes (scene
  ids, district names, ship classes,
  faction names, special-NPC ids, ...).
  PR review question: does this change
  add a string literal in engine/ that
  only makes sense for UC Life? If yes,
  push it down to data/.
end note

note bottom of L_UI
  Known gap: ui/ today contains hardcoded
  zh-CN player-facing strings. The seam
  shown here describes the target split,
  not 100% of HEAD's content placement.
  Future content-extraction work will move
  player-facing copy into data/ behind a
  string-id indirection; ui/ stays engine.
end note

note right of L_REND
  render/ has its own internal seam:
   - Game.tsx + ground/PixiGroundRenderer
     (ECS snapshot -> pixi)
   - sprite/ (LPC composer, anim ticker)
   - portrait/ (FC pregmod port -- opaque
     core, UC owns bridge + adapter)
  See 005_render_flow + 006_portrait_pipeline
  in arch/current/ for the unchanged shape.
end note

@enduml
